FBIS3-47050 "dreas006__a94028" FBIS-EAS-94-006-A Document Type:Daily Report 10 January 1994 ANNEX Mongolia Customs Service Technically Strengthened OW0601203794 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1901 GMT 6 Jan 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW0601203794 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Ulaanbaatar, January 6 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- Mongolia in the last two years is paying a great attention to the strengthening of the country's customs service, providing it with new technical means. As the deputy-chairman of the Central Custom's Department of Mongolia Ya. Erhembayar informed the MONTSAME correspondent, the customs service on the whole is provided with computers and other technical means, and in the first quarter of the current year the work on switching them to the united network with centralized control panel will be accomplished. In the new year the works will be continued on the international project "asicuda" on workout customs information. To raise qualification and professional skill of customs inspectors the training courses are organized within the country and abroad, he said.
